name: Jaran Kepang
description:
Jaran Kepang is a dance art that is played with the property in the form of an imitation horse, which is made of woven bamboo It is said that the Jaran Kepang dance is a trance dance. There is also a version that says that the Jaran Kepang dance depicts the story of a beautiful youth troop with the title Jathil riding a white horse. Regardless of its origin and historical value, Jaran Kepang reflects the spirit of heroism and the military aspect of a cavalry or cavalry troop. This can be seen from the rhythmic, dynamic, and aggressive movements, through the waving of woven bamboo, imitating the movements of a horse in the midst of war.
